post_text: We are excited to welcome students back to school on Tuesday, September 8th. We will be running our regular bus route times and pick up locations. School begins at 8:30 and dismisses at 3:30 daily. Students will be provided their own school supplies that will be kept in their desk or lockers. We do not recommend sending backpacks this year. Cutting down on the amount of items brought to and from school will help to keep the school environment safer for everyone. Facemasks will be provided to students as they board the bus. All students must wear a facemask while riding in school buses and vehicles. We’re all looking forward to starting a great school year! http://edl.io/n1290976

post_text:
Lunch Pickup available for Remote Online Learners - Wakpala Public School will be offering lunches, for pickup, to our students enrolled in remote online learning. Lunches for the entire week, can be picked up at the school each Monday. You must call the front office each Monday from 7-10 a.m. to place your order. Pickup will be from 10-11:30 a.m. each Monday using the East door on the front of the building (to the right of the canopy. You will be required to provide your student's PIN number in order to pick up the food. The PIN number is our way of verifying the student & eliminating duplication of meals.
Monday, September 7th, is a holiday so ordering & pickup will be pushed back to Tuesday, September 8th. The same times apply. http://edl.io/n1290359

post_text:
Athletic Guidelines 2020-2021

1. Athletes are unable to participate in two sports at one time. Athletes must choose to either participate in Cross Country or Volleyball.
2. Athletes must complete 10 full practices before being allowed to compete.
3. Athletes must start practice for their designated sport before Friday, August 28, 2020 in order to be considered part of the team. Athletes will not be able to join a sport after this date.
4. Athletes who participate in sports are required to attend scheduled practices. Missing practice for outside obligations (i.e. work) will result in an unexcused absence. Missing practice for family reasons will result in an excused absence.

These guidelines have been approved by the Athletics Director and will be implemented immediately. http://edl.io/n1279353

post_text: Wakpala School plans to reopen with first day of school on August 20, 2020. In light of COVID, a Re-opening Planning Committee has been established and is working on a Re-opening Safety Plan. The committee includes school board members, school administration, teachers, parents/guardians and an SRST Council Representative. The Plan will include safety strategies covering areas of: wearing of face masks and shields, physical distancing, frequent handwashing, temperature checks, cleaning and sanitizing, classroom desk configurations, in-person classroom instruction, on-line remote learning, communication, food service and transportation protocols. As the Safety Plan is finalized, it will be shared with all parties. Stayed tuned! http://edl.io/n1257345

NOTICE OF PUBLIC HEARING
January 8, 2020
Indian Policies & Procedures

NOTICE IS HEREBY GIVEN of the intention of the Smee School District Board of Education to hold a public hearing on Indian Policies & Procedures which ensures that Indian children participate on an equal basis with non-Indian children served by the LEA.

The public hearing will be held on January 8, 2020, at 7:00 p.m. in the Library of the Wakpala School, 12250 SD Hwy 1806, Wakpala, South Dakota 57658. At such time, the comments of all interested persons regarding the subject of Indian Polices & Procedures will be heard.

• 18th and 19th- after school at 3:30
• Friday Dec. 27th- 1:00 to 3:30 reg. practice

Students will have to find their own rides to and from school during Christmas break. There will also be scrimmages during the holidays.
